data.chText: 神经紧张的；担心的；不能松弛的
data.enText: nervous or worried, and unable to relax

data.chText: 他是个神经非常紧张的人。
data.enText: He's a very tense person.

data.chText: 她的声音听起来又气又急。
data.enText: She sounded tense and angry.

data.chText: 令人紧张的（或焦虑的、满腹愤懑的等）

before.enText: of a situation, an event, a period of time, etc.

data.enText: in which people have strong feelings such as worry, anger, etc. that often cannot be expressed openly

data.chText: 等候测试结果的这几个星期里我寝食不安。
data.enText: I spent a tense few weeks waiting for the results of the tests.

data.chText: 会议的气氛越来越紧张。
data.enText: The atmosphere in the meeting was getting more and more tense.

before.enText: of a muscle or other part of the body

data.enText: tight rather than relaxed

data.chText: 按摩会使紧张的肌肉松弛。
data.enText: A massage will relax those tense muscles.
stretched tightly
produced with the muscles of the speech organs stretched tight
any of the forms of a verb that may be used to show the time of the action or state expressed by the verb

data.chText: 过去 / 现在 / 将来时态
data.enText: the past/present/future tense
if you tense your muscles, or you or your muscles tense , they become tight and stiff, especially because you are not relaxed

data.chText: 他准备起跑时肌肉绷紧了。
data.enText: His muscles tensed as he got ready to run.

data.chText: 再次听到那个奇怪的声音，她紧张起来。
data.enText: She tensed, hearing the strange noise again.

data.chText: 眼看要挨打，她绷紧了肌肉。
data.enText: She tensed her muscles in anticipation of the blow.

data.chText: 他竖起耳朵谛听是否有人跟踪。
data.enText: He tensed himself, listening to see if anyone had followed him.
be/get tensed up

data.chText: 变得神经紧张；变得焦虑不安
data.enText: to become or feel nervous or worried so that you cannot relax

means: 令人紧张的(或焦虑的、满腹愤懑的等)

ex.zh: 将来/过去/完成/现在时态

data.enText: be/get tensed up

data.chText: 变得神经紧张；变得焦虑不安
data.enText: to become or feel nervous or worried so that you cannot relax

tr: a grammatical category of verbs used to express distinctions of time
cause to be tense and uneasy or nervous or anxious
example: he got a phone call from his lawyer that tensed him up
He tensed up when he saw his opponent enter the room
alternately relax and tense your calf muscle
tense the rope manually before tensing the spring

tr: become stretched or tense or taut
"the rope strained when the weight was attached"
pronounced with relatively tense tongue muscles (e.g., the vowel sound in `beat')
in or of a state of physical or nervous tension

value.def: A tense situation or period of time is one that makes people anxious, because they do not know what is going to happen next.

example.ex: This gesture of goodwill did little to improve the tense atmosphere at the talks...
example.tran: 这一友好姿态基本上没有改善会谈的紧张气氛。

example.ex: After three very tense weeks he phoned again...
example.tran: 过了紧张不安的 3 个星期，他又一次打来电话。
有一阵令人局促不安的沉默。

value.tran: (局势、时期)令人紧张的，让人焦虑的

value.def: If you are tense, you are anxious and nervous and cannot relax.

example.ex: Dart, who had at first been very tense, at last relaxed.
example.tran: 起初，达特非常紧张，最后终于放松了下来。

value.tran: 紧张的;焦虑的;无法放松的

example.ex: She waited tensely for the next bulletin...
example.tran: 她焦虑地等候着下一期公告。

example.ex: 'Tony, I can explain everything,' she said tensely.
example.tran: “托尼，这一切我都可以解释，”她紧张地说。

example.ex: McKay walked slowly toward this screen, feeling a growing tenseness.
example.tran: 麦凯缓缓地朝这个屏幕走来，每走一步心情都更加紧张。

value.def: If your body is tense, your muscles are tight and not relaxed.

example.ex: She lay, eyes shut, body tense...
example.tran: 她躺着，双目紧闭，全身绷直。

example.ex: A bath can relax tense muscles.
example.tran: 洗个澡可以放松紧张的肌肉。

example.ex: If you feel a tenseness around the eyes, relax your muscles.
example.tran: 你要是觉得两眼周围紧绷，就放松一下肌肉。

value.def: If your muscles tense, if you tense, or if you tense your muscles, your muscles become tight and stiff, often because you are anxious or frightened.

example.ex: He tensed as the big West Indian gripped his shoulder...
example.tran: 那个大块头西印度群岛土著人抓住他的肩膀时，他浑身紧张起来。

example.ex: Jane tensed her muscles to stop them from shaking.
example.tran: 简把肌肉绷紧，不让它们颤抖。

example.ex: When we are under stress our bodies tend to tense up...
example.tran: 人一紧张，身体就会变僵硬。

example.ex: I tried not to tense up, or become obviously wary...
example.tran: 我尽量不让自己紧张，或者表现得非常警觉。

example.ex: Tense up the muscles in both of your legs.

value.def: The tense of a verb group is its form, which usually shows whether you are referring to past, present, or future time.

example.ex: It was as though Corinne was already dead: they were speaking of her in the past tense.
example.tran: 科琳娜好像已经去世了：他们谈论她时用的是过去时。

trans: 将来/过去/完成/现在时态
